						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Memblers wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Pretty much everyone tests on emulators, and there's the whole chicken before the egg problem when it comes to emulator support.</div><br /><br />If it's just about testing (as opposed to wide support for the mapper on common emulators for a rom release), it seems that the community is pretty quick to add support for a new mapper if it's compelling enough. Mesen and FCEUX both support most of your GTROM functionality by now, and I imagine if you came out with a new mapper that was really compelling (both cheap and powerful), people would be interested enough in using it that SOMEBODY would make emulator support happen.</div>

					
